We partnered with @mountaindew & @pepsico to build a custom wall ride feature in Park Lane, made of recycled plastic bottles and snack wrappers, as part of our commitment to achieve zero waste to landfill by 2030. Learn more at the EpicPromise link in our bio.

node.text:
Snow is piling up and we know that means everyone is eager to get into the High Alpine. We're getting closer but we're not quite there yet... In the meantime, while our teams work hard to prepare new terrain, we wanted to give you an inside look at the massive amount of work and team effort it takes to safely open new terrain after new snowfall in this video we made last winter.
 
Keep up your snow dances, be patient and thank our incredible mountain operations teams! We'll be skiing and riding more soon!
📹: @ryansheetz

With the season in sight, we wanted to share a quick refresher: Priority Reservation Days vs. Week-Of Reservation Days. 
 
▪️Priority Reservation Days: On Nov. 6, you will be able to make reservations for the core season (Dec. 8 – April 4) across all of our resorts. As a pass holder, you can lock in up to 7 Priority Reservation Days for the core season in advance, and as many week-of reservations during the season as your pass type and availability allow.
 
▪️Week-Of Reservation Days: As our resorts start to open for the season, you can also take advantage of exclusive early season access by making week-of reservations. Booking a week-of reservation does not count against your Priority Reservation Days for the core season.  
 
While the first few days will likely see higher volume and extended wait times, there’s no need to rush to lock in your days! We designed this exclusive month-long booking window to accommodate our pass holders' requests before lift tickets go on sale on Dec. 8.
 
Take a sneak peek of our new reservation system above!

node.text:
Freedom and Independence. 

Two words that go together like Peanut Butter and Jelly. Macaroni and Cheese. Batman and Robin.

Coming this winter, a brand-new chair creates a classic pair on Peak 7 - Freedom and Independence. The new Freedom SuperChair, alongside the existing Independence SuperChair, will provide guests the opportunity to experience the wide-open and rolling terrain of Peak 7 in a whole new way, and carve their own path down and across our expansive peaks.

The new Freedom SuperChair is set to debut for the upcoming winter and our 60th anniversary season.

node.text: Serving up a heavy pour! Here's an inside look at the first concrete pour taking place as we begin to set the tower foundations for our new Peak 7 Chairlift. Coming winter 2021-2022, the new chair will be a game-changer for Peak 7 and the resort experience.

node.text: It was all smiles out here for opening weekend! Thanks to everyone who helped kick off our summer season of Epic Discovery! We're open daily through Labor Day and will have more activities opening as we head into the Fourth of July holiday weekend.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Breckenridge Ski Resort on June 16, 2021. May be an image of ski slope.

node.text: Summer operations launch this Friday with the return of Epic Discovery and the opening of Peak 8 Base Camp and the BreckConnect Gondola! Open activities will include the Alpine Slides, Gold Runner Coaster, Mini Golf, Bungee Trampolines, Gemstone Panning and our Kids Zipline, Ropes Course and Summer Tubing. With on-going mountain prep work, additional activities are set to open ahead of the Fourth of July holiday weekend, including scenic rides and bike hauls on the Colorado SuperChair, and activities at Alpine Camp.

node.text: Summer is just around the corner, and we can't wait for beautiful sunny days and adventures in the high alpine! What summer activities are you most looking forward to? ⛰️😎
